From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 15:27:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] selftests/bpf: avoid trace_printk in arena spin lock
 fallbacks

arena_spin_lock.bpf.o uses the arena spin-lock helpers from a TC
program. The helper implementation has bpf_printk() calls after
cond_break fallback labels that are intended to catch unexpected loop
termination.

Even though these paths are not expected to run, the verifier still
validates them when arena_spin_lock_slowpath() is a global function. TC
programs cannot use bpf_trace_printk(), so the otherwise valid
arena_spin_lock.bpf.o program is rejected while processing the helper's
fallback path.

Drop the printk calls and return the last observed lock value from the
fallback path. The loop remains bounded for the verifier, and the helper
stays usable from program types that cannot call bpf_trace_printk().

Signed-off-by: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
---
 .../selftests/bpf/libarena/include/bpf_arena_spin_lock.h      | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/libarena/include/bpf_arena_spin_lock.h b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/libarena/include/bpf_arena_spin_lock.h
index 16916365cfd9..afeb951d021f 100644
--- a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/libarena/include/bpf_arena_spin_lock.h
+++ b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/libarena/include/bpf_arena_spin_lock.h
@@ -170,7 +170,6 @@ static __always_inline u32 xchg_tail(arena_spinlock_t __arena *lock, u32 tail)
 
 	return old;
 out:
-	bpf_printk("RUNTIME ERROR: %s unexpected cond_break exit!!!", __func__);
 	return old;
 }
 
@@ -226,7 +225,6 @@ u32 arena_fetch_set_pending_acquire(arena_spinlock_t __arena *lock)
 
 	return old;
 out:
-	bpf_printk("RUNTIME ERROR: %s unexpected cond_break exit!!!", __func__);
 	return old;
 }
 
